text: ALL UTILITIES ARE IN!!! Bring your house plans to life on this peaceful 5-acre retreat, bordered by government-owned forestland and surrounded by nature. A HUGE 1, 808 sq ft, 2-bay shop is already in place. (Unpermitted shop addition to the left of the building - will either need to be demolished or approved with a retroactive permit.) All the outbuildings are there a chicken coop, greenhouse, woodshed, and even RV parking! Perfect for starting your homestead or hobby farm with buildable site further up the property. The building site has valley views, nature, and has already been cleared. The seller had plans to build, but health forces sale. Now its your turn to create the life you've always envisioned.

Back on the Market! Escape to your own private oasis with this stunning log cabin, nestled on 4.77 acres of beautifully landscaped land. This property offers a perfect blend of rustic charm and modern convenience, making it an ideal retreat for nature lovers and outdoor enthusiasts. Cozy and inviting, featuring open living spaces, natural wood finishes, and plenty of natural light. Lots of lush greenery, mature trees, fruit trees, and a designated gardening space for your green thumb. The 1680 sq. ft. shop provides ample space for all your tools and toysperfect for hobbies, storage, or a workshop PLUS RV Parking.

Welcome to this cozy & affordable home nestled in the sought-after Skagit Highlands community. With a practical layout & open-concept design, this property provides comfortable living spaces filled with natural light, ideal for both entertaining & relaxing. Fresh interior paint and a well-maintained exterior allow you to move right in! The Skagit Highlands community features scenic walking trails, parks, & playgrounds for the community. Enjoy this homes prime location, just minutes from I-5, offering a convenient commute & quick access to shopping, dining, schools, and the charming downtown Mt. Vernon area. If youre looking for a welcoming, low-maintenance home in a vibrant community setting, this property is a must see.

text: Welcome to this wonderful 4-bedroom home in Sauk Mountain View Estates North, ideally perched on the green belt! Enjoy the close proximity to town, all amenities, and the scenic walking trails at Northern State. This home truly offers the perfect blend of convenience and comfort.

Investor Alert! Duplex in Old Town! BOTH UNITS ARE REMODELED! Live in one and rent the other. What a great place to stay after a weekend of boating! 1107- 2 bedrooms 1 bath Remodeled 2014. Vaulted ceilings, large open living room with brick fireplace. Opens to dining area and kitchen w/skylight. New cabinets, granite counters and back splash. Carport that could be enclosed. 1109-2 bedroom 1 bath-remodeled 2024 with all new flooring, trim and paint. Awesome large kitchen w/dining area includes new cabinets, quartz counters and all new appliances. Nice size bedrooms and walk-in closet. Live the dream of Old Town! Just blocks to Cap Sante Marina, lots of wonderful restaurants! 1400 sq ft strip across alley also conveys.

Cedar Ridge Estates with private access to Sixteen Lake with Dock & Boat Launch. Approx 2, 155 SF Rambler on a private 1.34 acres. Home features 3BR, 2.5BA, Greatroom with gas fireplace, wall of windows & door to large deck. Kitchen w/island, Corian countertops, pantry & breakfast nook. Dining off entry way. The primary suite w/gas fireplace for cozy ambiance, sitting area, walk-in closet, access to back deck, & relaxing jetted tub. Large back deck provides ample space to enjoy the sunset views. The home is light and bright, with a wall of windows that allows natural light to flood the interior. Fruit trees & berry bushes add a charming, natural element. Spacious 4-car garage w/ample storage & parking. Outstanding Conway School K-8th!

Welcome to affordable Old Town Living in this 1916 single-level home ready for new memories to be made. First time on market in decades and move-in ready! Wonderful, level entry with gardens. The large living area has a gas fireplace and large windows. The bathroom has a walk-in tub / shower in place, providing easy access. The kitchen has a walk-in pantry and plenty of space including a skylight to brighten up the room even more. The dining area is large, and large windows overlook the back patio and completely fenced back yard. There is potential for future parking from the alley in this large back yard space. The workshop space is excellent for storage or hobbies and could possibly be converted or re-built into a garage.

Spacious 3 bed/2 bath single level home w/attached garage & RV parking in established MV neighborhood - out of the floodplain. This oversized corner lot offers plenty of room for outdoor entertaining w/two patios, yard & garden space. Storage shed. Solid built home w/good-sized rooms just waiting for your updates. Open kitchen w/dining nook, center island, wall ovens, great view. Family room off kitchen leads to back yard. A huge formal living area at the front of the house features picture windows and lots of room for all your gatherings. Generous primary suite has wall of closets and attached private bath. Two guest bedrooms and additional full bath. Garage has extra deep bay for storage or workshop area. Separate RV driveway.

text: Discover your own slice of paradise with this affordable, move-in ready property on 5 acres! text: This custom-built 3-bedroom, 2-bath home is perfect for horses or car collectors alike offering stunning views and 5 flat usable acres. 48x30 shop/garage with five roll-up doors, and a 38x36 three-stall horse barn with cement floor, an office equipped with a wood stove, and small hayloft. This single-story house showcases intricate details: skylights, vaulted ceilings, arched doorways, freestanding wood stove, Heat Pump, hardwood, laminate flooring, ash cabinets, pantry and a large eat up kitchen island. The primary bedroom includes a gas fireplace, on suite bathroom with a jetted tub and 4-foot walk in shower. Large front and rear decks for relaxation and elk watching. The property is fully cross-fenced, and beautifully landscaped.

Adorable country rambler located in the area of Lyman! Walk through the front door & you are welcomed into the livingroom which features a cozy pellet stove. A dining area can be found as well with a sliding glass door leading to a covered back deck. Two bedrooms & a full bathroom are on one end of the home while the kitchen sits on the other. A bonus room with a wood burning fireplace can be found beside the kitchen which can be used as an office or bedroom if desired. Large laundry room also with access to the garage! Head outside to a spacious back yard complete with a covered patio, chicken coop, & seasonal creek with a bridge! There is a large shop right next to the home, offering ample storage & space for hobbies. Come call it home!
